<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-04-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-04-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="338" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d338">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 24074/3.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Vice and Deputy Consul General <persName type="from">Baugh</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Hankow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-22"><hi rend="italic">April 22,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Baugh reports serious disturbances Hunan missions and the destruction
                            of Chang-sha customhouse and business houses, Says missionaries have
                            been summoned from the interior, that foreign war vessels have been
                            dispatched to Chang-sha, and that the legation has been fully
                            informed.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>